\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces Schematic overview of CAPO. (a) Within-trajectory token dependence induces nontrivial covariance structure in trajectory gradients, which can amplify gradient variance as a function of response length. (b) CAPO reweights trajectories by learned posterior precisions (length and covariance-aware) to obtain an unbiased, lower-variance aggregate update.\relax }}{3}{figure.caption.1}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {2}{\ignorespaces Bayesian plate model for CAPO with Empirical Bayes length and dependence estimation. Global hyperparameters \((\mu ,\sigma ^2,\beta ,\xi )\) govern the heteroscedastic Normal model \(g_i\mid L_i,\mu ,\sigma ^2,\beta ,\xi \sim \mathcal N(\mu ,\sigma ^2 L_i^{\beta }s(L_i;\xi ))\) and the token-level dependence structure of \(Y_{i,\tau }\). The induced variance \(v_i(\vartheta )=\sigma ^2 L_i^{\beta }s(L_i;\xi )\) and precision \(\omega _i(\beta ,\xi )=[L_i^{\beta }s(L_i;\xi )]^{-1}\) yield trajectory weights \(w_i(\beta ,\xi )\propto \omega _i(\beta ,\xi )\) and the CAPO aggregator \(m(\beta ,\xi )=\DOTSB \sum@ \slimits@ _i w_i(\beta ,\xi )g_i\), which is used in the policy/teacher update.\relax }}{5}{figure.caption.2}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {3}{\ignorespaces Training dynamics (validation Avg@8 vs. global step) for a representative subset of methods.\relax }}{44}{figure.caption.15}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4}{\ignorespaces Stability summary. Each point corresponds to a method, plotted by monotonicity (higher is better) and negative drift rate (lower is better).\relax }}{45}{figure.caption.17}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {5}{\ignorespaces Verifier success by response-length decile. This analysis highlights whether a method disproportionately favors short (or long) trajectories even when end-to-end accuracy is similar.\relax }}{46}{figure.caption.18}%
